</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,261,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,334,360]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Notes on morphology.</emphasis>
Body of moderate size (TL 
<quantity box="[771,860,333,360]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
), brown, each elytron with two round concavities in apical portion (
<figureCitation box="[320,406,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1352,1377]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1302]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[153,1438,181,1302]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Calvariopsis gen. nov., group I (A, C, E–F) and group II (B, D), females, apical portion of elytra, excitators. A) C. pittieri; B) C. brasiliense, an arrow indicates patch of modified setae; C) C. sp., Colombia, Gorgona Island; D) C. sp., Ecuador, an arrow indicates patch of modified setae; E) C. sp., Paraguay; F) C. sp., Peru." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783720/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
), small hooked tuft of setae present in adsutural portion of each elytron. Bursal sclerite missing in the studied specimen, only ovipositor and sternite VIII present. Gonocoxites widely triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1423,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,195,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[151,1436,195,1889]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 27. Calvariopsis gen. nov., females. A–B) C. sp., Bolivia; C–D) C. sp., Colombia; E–G) C. sp., Costa Rica; H) C. sp., Ecuador; I) C. sp., Ecuador; J) C. sp., French Guiana; K) C. sp., Panama; L) C. sp., Paraguay; M) C. sp., Peru. A, H, I–M) genital tract; B, G) bursal sclerite; C), E) ovipositor; D, F) sternite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783802/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
), with subapical gonostyli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,261,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,478,504]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</emphasis>
Included in group I due to the following characters: elytra with distinct foveate excitators, wide gonocoxites with subapical gonostyli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
